{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17585429","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17585429"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:11:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:11:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14973"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14973","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14973"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.21,0.18,0.44,0.03,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7661"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64395"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7661","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7661"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14973"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49827"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7882"},{"type":"tags","id":"8112"},{"type":"tags","id":"9885"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18732"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18735"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21199"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64395","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64395"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ELymphoedema is a condition characterised by swelling due to the accumulation of lymph fluid in the tissues. It can result from various causes, including infections, malignancies and surgical procedures.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most likely to cause lymphoedema?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Chronic venous insufficiency","Congestive heart failure","Elephantiasis","Hypothyroidism","Sarcoidosis"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElephantiasis\u003C/strong\u003E is a condition caused by parasitic infections, such as those from filarial worms, which can lead to lymphoedema. The parasites block the lymphatic vessels, causing fluid accumulation and swelling. This is a common cause of lymphoedema in endemic areas, particularly in tropical and subtropical regions (Image 1). Clinically, it manifests as severe swelling, often in the lower limbs, and can lead to significant disability.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESarcoidosis\u003C/strong\u003E can cause lymphadenopathy but is not typically associated with lymphoedema. It primarily affects the lungs and lymph nodes, leading to granuloma formation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECongestive heart failure\u003C/strong\u003E can cause oedema due to fluid overload, but this is typically pitting oedema and affects both legs symmetrically, rather than causing lymphoedema.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic venous insufficiency\u003C/strong\u003E leads to venous stasis and pitting oedema, often with skin changes such as varicosities and hyperpigmentation, rather than lymphoedema. (Image 2)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E can cause myxoedema, which is a type of non-pitting oedema, but it does not typically cause lymphoedema. The swelling in hypothyroidism is due to mucopolysaccharide deposition rather than lymphatic obstruction. (Image 3)\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Lymphoedema can be caused by a variety of conditions, including parasitic infections, cancer, and surgical interventions.","Elephantiasis is a condition caused by parasitic infections that can lead to lymphoedema.","Elephantiasis is commonly caused by filarial worms and is prevalent in tropical and subtropical regions."],"references":["Bona, C. A., \u0026 Bonilla, F. A. (2019). Textbook of immunology. CRC press","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Yimer M, Hailu T, Mulu W, Abera B. Epidemiology of elephantiasis with special emphasis on podoconiosis in Ethiopia: A literature review. J Vector Borne Dis. 2015 Jun;52(2):111-5. PMID: 26119541.","Nutman TB. Insights into the pathogenesis of disease in human lymphatic filariasis. Lymphat Res Biol. 2013 Sep;11(3):144-8. doi: 10.1089/lrb.2013.0021. PMID: 24044755; PMCID: PMC3780283."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49827"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14973"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21217"},{"type":"media","id":"21218"},{"type":"media","id":"21219"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21217","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21217"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/AngIuZlfziJPS3oCGg9KvUrB7HO5AK.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/AngIuZlfziJPS3oCGg9KvUrB7HO5AK.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"21218","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21218"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/cTuFiq9vDRYm83x9TjBUAFyLVySYtS.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/cTuFiq9vDRYm83x9TjBUAFyLVySYtS.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":1125}},{"type":"media","id":"21219","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21219"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/WvAxRIiuQKAnwqJG7Mz2PwxU7SqDDq.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/WvAxRIiuQKAnwqJG7Mz2PwxU7SqDDq.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":768,"height":1024}},{"type":"item